      "body" : "The expected behavior is that when listen=0 is set, the node doesn't relay blocks and hence uses minimal bandwidth.  This is documented in many places, including https://bitcoin.org/en/full-node#disable-listening. I see now that maxuploadtarget=0 means unlimited bandwidth, when I added it to my conf that setting wasn't documented, so I'm now removing it. But listen=0 should have still overridden that.",
